<dl id="n15047d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15047d">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15047d"> 47(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Speaker = Talker / = Tales</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the summer of 1214 Snorre thought seriously of going to Norway; but in the meantime rumours reached Iceland that the Earl was dead, and the scald postponed his visit. His skill in the law was so well known that in 1215 Snorre was chosen <mark>Law-speaker</mark> or President of the Althing. <small> Snorri Sturluson, <a name="SSHK" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SSHK"><cite title="source">Heimskringla: the Olaf Sagas</cite></a>, (1915) ?xi</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15223d" href="c15all.htm#c15223d">VI.C.15:223(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
